<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in a spot • in spots</xh5><p> <i>in a spot</i>—(coll.) in a difficult situation; in trouble: We really are <u>in a spot</u>, because to refuse her would cause months, if not years, of pouting and hard feelings.</p><p> <i>in spots</i>—<i>(U.S. sl.)</i> occasionally; at intervals: A boatman being asked how he managed to secure sleeping time, answered, “I sleep <u>in spots</u>”; that is, at intervals, by snatches.</p> </entry>
